freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Definite gastric distressbelching, gas, zero appetite. Perhaps just coincidental, but also tired and unmotivated to do much. Have had 1 cup of tea and a handful of saltine crackers.
I had mold reflux and nausea this am, at 46 hours post injection. It mostly resolved within a few hours. The reflux is highly unusual for me. Still have mild indigestion. Could be coincidence.
Is it unusual to have a less intense reaction to second dose?  Or is there a possibility the dose was compromised?
Pain abated with slow and thorough stretching of muscles and fascia. Minimal/negligible pain following stretches.

Perhaps coincidental - but the uncharacteristic reflux m reappeared along with a first-ever globes sensation  that started at 4 a.m. and persisted until about 7 a.m.  LES dysfunction has persisted all day.
Upper GI concerns mostly, but not completely resolved.
